The paper deals with the problem of detecting unsolvable queries in definite logic programs, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and logic (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the use of abductive search, which is a technique commonly used in programming languages and compilers (cs.PL). Additionally, the paper presents methods for efficiently searching the space of pre-interpretations, which is a topic related to software engineering (cs.SE) and databases (cs.DB).
